  "texts": [
    "Pattison (2008), for instance, has suggested a day-long workshop format (originally designed for the French Network of the Institute of Translation and Interpreting in the United Kingdom).",
    "The workshop progresses from focused word associations and detailed/concrete description exercises, to comparative discussion of literary techniques in originals and their translations (e.g.",
    "repetitions, 'hooks' in a story), to bilingual keywording for character creation and, finally, to writing for a specific audience.",
    "The module we are proposing aims to cultivate knowledge of the richness of language and theoretical ties between translation and writing over a course of eleven weeks.",
    "This proposal is intended to explain how to create a basic course that could, of course, be adapted to different institutions and time lengths or even be adapted to individual seminars."
  ],
